		<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://blog.cedricbonhomme.org/2012/09/12/systemd-init-et-upstart/" rel="bookmark">systemd, init et upstart</a></h1>
		<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="entry-date"><a href="http://blog.cedricbonhomme.org/2012/09/12/systemd-init-et-upstart/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2012-09-12T08:14:09+00:00">September 12, 2012</time></a></span> <span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://blog.cedricbonhomme.org/author/cedric/" rel="author">Cédric</a></span></span>		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

		<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Si en ce moment tu es un peu perdu entre systemd, init et upstart (plus udev, D-Bus, DCOP, etc.), je pense que <a href="http://linuxfr.org/news/le-point-sur-udev-et-systemd">ce billet</a> sera d&#8217;une bonne aide.</p>
<p>Pour avoir de bonnes informations à propos de systemd:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://0pointer.de/blog/projects/watchdog.html">systemd for Administrators, Part XV</a>;</li>
<li><a href="http://0pointer.de/blog/projects/self-documented-boot.html">systemd for Administrators, Part XIV</a>;</li>
<li><a href="http://0pointer.de/blog/projects/warsaw.html">Presentation in Warsaw</a>;</li>
<li><a href="http://0pointer.de/blog/projects/systemctl-journal.html">systemd for Administrators, Part XIII</a>;</li>
<li><a href="http://0pointer.de/blog/projects/multi-seat.html">The Most Awesome, Least-Advertised Fedora 17 Feature</a>;</li>
<li>et d&#8217;autres sur le <a href="http://0pointer.de/blog/">même blog</a> ou sur la page <a href="https://plus.google.com/u/0/104232583922197692623/posts">Google +</a>.</li>
</ul>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
